          "[Exam, IN_Sem1, IN_Sem2, IN_Sem3, IN_Sem4, IN_Sem5, IN_Sem6, IN_Sem6, InPc]",
          "Before Final Exam",
          "Authors use a model based on GRU. The data is modeled as a having multiple features.\n\nAs a start, the authors start with the creation of a fully connected layer which is then given as argument to the GRU, whose outputs are subsequently given to a MaxPooling layer followed by a Dense Layer which does the predictions. ",
          "RNN, ARD V.2, AdaBoost, GRU_Based",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{Accuracy: 0.997 - GRU_Based, Precision: 0.986 - GRU_Based, Recall: 0.963 - GRU_Based, F1-Score: 0.974- GRU_Based}",
          "This paper is not very good. IT presents multiple imprecisions when it comes to techniques (AdaBoost is presented as standard Bagging) and descriptions (k-Fold of 1). \n\nAuthors create a GRU-based model and do benchmarking.\n\n",
          "- Technical errors on description of some of the models (e.g. AdaBoost)\n\n- K-Fold of 1?\n\n- No Ablation study\n\n- Limited exploration of models found in the literature.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 7
    }
